---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import DonateStrip from "../components/DonateStrip.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — The Askesis Project"
  description="What the Askesis Project is, and why it exists."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <section class="about-content">
      <span class="section-label">About</span>
      <h1>What is askesis?</h1>

      <div class="body-text">
        <p>
          The ancient Greeks had a word, <em>askēsis</em>, for the kind of
          disciplined practice that shapes a person from the inside. It began as
          a term from athletics — the daily repetition of physical training —
          and was gradually claimed by philosophers who saw that the same logic
          applied to the cultivation of character.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Stoics practiced poverty days, cold baths, and fasting — not from
          asceticism for its own sake, but to test themselves against their own
          philosophy. Ignatius of Loyola gave the word to the Western spiritual
          tradition. It eventually gave us "ascetic." But at its root,
          <em>askēsis</em> was simply about practice: the belief that who you are
          is something you can work on.
        </p>
        <p>
          This publication is built on that belief. It is an attempt to think
          seriously about self-cultivation — not as self-improvement in the
          contemporary sense, but in the older, more demanding sense: the
          formation of a person capable of living well.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <DonateStrip />
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-content {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 6rem 2.5rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0.75rem 0 2.5rem;
  }

  .body-text p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-cream-72);
  }

  .body-text p + p {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .body-text em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .about-content {
      padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 1.9rem;
    }
  }
</style>
